A man who allegedly ran an illicit licensing and police clearance operation has been arrested with almost R5.3-million in cash at his home in Cape Town.Several identity documents and two vehicles were also seized during a search of the man s home in the suburb of Belhar on Sunday.The 33-year-old suspect was nabbed following an investigation by the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation in conjunction with the Department of Transport.He faces charges of money laundering corruption and racketeering and will appear in the Bellville Magistrate s Court on Tuesday said Hawks spokesman Captain Lloyd Ramovha.Acting Head of the Hawks in the Western Cape Brigadier Mzwandile Ndlovu said: This is undoubtedly a telling blow to the underworld we remain unequivocal in the fight against organised crime. TMG Digital